items.name: Juggernaut
items.description:
Hello my friends, are you ready for one last ride with Stable Diffusion 1.5 and "Juggernaut Aftermath"?

I actually announced that I would not release another version for SD 1.5. However, there were some updates and information that I didn't want to withhold from you. You can find the recipe for the model at the end.

First, I want to thank you for over 70k runs on Tensor Art and for nearly 10k downloads of the final Juggernaut version here on CivitAi. Your images under the model are a huge motivation for me to continue working on Juggernaut.

Now a note about the Juggernaut XL version:

Without financial support, it is currently not possible for me to simply train Juggernaut for SDXL. However, in order to be able to do this in the future, I have taken on some larger contracts which I am now working through to secure the safety and financial background to fully concentrate on Juggernaut XL afterwards. I don't want to just present you with a slapped together unfinished version with which I would probably be totally dissatisfied myself. Therefore, the release of Juggernaut XL will probably be postponed a bit (aiming for early September).

Lastly, the recipe for the last Juggernaut version on SD 1.5:

SD 1.5 Base

Training Set 1 (0.65)

Absolute Reality (0.18)

epiCRealism V3 (0.2)

Humans (0.15)

Skin Enhancer (0.15)

Better Portrait Lighting (0.2)

Training Set 2 (0.55)

RPG 5 (0.38)

Divas (0.15)

And of course the NinjaFix made by @chillpixel

Thanks all those Creators for their hard work :)

Of Course you can run "Juggernaut" on Tensor.Art

items.description:
Please consider supporting me so I can continue to make more Models / LoRA's for the community! --> Buy Me A Coffee

This model was trained on Furry Vixens v2.0

This model is mainly trained for Anthro's, but it does small Chibi's too. It's trained for both male / female Braixens, so it should do both fairly easy.


Be sure to use the tags "gynomorph, breasts" for generating females, and "andromorph, flat chest" when you want to generate male Braixens. The tag "penis" is interchangeable for both, and there's also some training for "bukkake, many dicks" if you want to have some group fun.

It works best at a weight of 0.7, though you can use 0.4 if you want to create more generic looking furries instead.

You can use these tags when generating images:

Braixen, Braixen ears, Braixen tail, red eyes

Be sure to use these settings!

Steps: 32

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

CFG scale: 7

Size: 384x512

Model: Furry Vixens v2

Denoising strength: 0.6

Clip skip: 2

Hires upscale: 2

Hires upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B

Here's an example prompt, though you can find others in the gallery.

Positive Prompt

(Braixen, Braixen ears, Braixen tail), (gynomorph:1.1), breasts, head turn, blushing, open mouth, tongue out, smile, red eyes, autumn, forest, trees <lora:Braixen v3-000006:0.7>

Osiris D3 2001

Baggy pants

2001 was also the year of baggy jeans, preferably sagged low and made from silvery shiny fabric. This LoRA can be used to end the skinny jeans era enshrined in the Stable Diffusion models. Use the trigger words baggy jeans or baggy pants to get those nice wide and loose pants. Add silver for a more shiny effect.

Infos

The LoRA was trained on SD 1.5 as base model, but works well on either realistic or anime models and can also be used very well for NSFW creations. Recommended strength is 1.

items.name: Fraux [Granblue Fantasy]
items.description:
Another addition in Granblue Fantasy collection. One of the least popular characters — The Devil companion Fraux is here.

I want to thank @Hollowstrawberry for the collab he made. And also @rockerBOO, @ChameleonAI, @zykurv, @IndolentCat for their tips and tricks! Check their creations as well!

The reviews and feedback will be very valuable for me.

The main trigger word:

  • gbfraux

To recreate her original outfit the next words in prompt will be useful:

  • robe or hooded robe, off shoulder for showing bare shoulders, leotard (however you can skip that if you want, most of the time it will still generate something close to her original leotard-like suit), thighhighs, gold trim for adding additional details, pendant choker and wide sleeves.

  • some models may sometimes fail to generate her ears, in this case I recommend adding animal ears to prompt to guarantee that, but most of the time it should work without it.

  • another words that you can experiment with are detached pants, short shorts, detached sleeves. i did not have much luck with those unfortunately.

  • i highly recommend adding simple background to negative prompt

Weights:

This LoRA was trained on AnyLora from @Lykon, so sweet spot for it is 0.7, however depending on the model you using you might want to adjust that. Especially if you will be trying to use it with realistic models.

I'm not sure what name LoRA will get on downloading, so please make sure you using the proper name in prompt of the file that you downloaded if you going to copy prompts from previews.

Negative embeddings:

Two negative embeddings were used in preview prompts:

  • AuroraNegative, you can find download link for it in description on this page: https://civitai.com/models/40199/aurora

  • badhandv4: https://civitai.com/models/16993/badhandv4-animeillustdiffusion

items.name: FGO Sprite Style
items.description:
This LoRA allows you to generate characters in the style of a Fate/Grand Order game sprite.

The LoRA was tested on various models, and the results were generally pretty unsatisfactory when used alone. I recommand using my other LoRA to replicate Ufotable artstyle, and, if you're using Automatic1111 webui, to turn on Highres. Fix ! With the Ufotable Lora and the Highres Fix, the generated images are much better than using the FGO Sprite LoRA alone. You can see the difference with the images of this post.

While using this LoRA, I recommand adding the fgo sprite tag to your prompt, to ensure to have only FGO Sprite style images.

The LoRA seems to give better results while using AnythingV5, but models like AnythingV4.5, AnythingV3 or NAI also work. It's up to you, to use the model you like the most.

The LoRA weight should be between 0.8 and 1.0, and I recommand using a 9:16 ratio, or something resembling it, since using a 1:1 ratio to generate an image let pretty much every model add some (really cool) effects in the background, or to simply generate multiple times the same character.

items.name: futapocalypse 1.0
items.description:
This is a futa model built from hundreds of hours of research and training attempts. It is using fluffyrock-768-lion-low-lr-e38-offset-noise-e6 as a base. the base model this was trained on can be found in this discord server: https://discord.gg/furrydiffusion

CFG goes from 4-20+, sample steps go from 20-150 on Euler A with depreciating gains after 80 steps from my tests.

it's using E621 tags, not dabooru. you can get the autocomplete extension in the SD webui exstensions tab, then in the options you can switch to E621 for easy autocomplete.

futanari is the keyword, but gynomorph also works (furry art generation is possible with this tag).

i did my best to add all the good stuff, breast sizes go from flat chested -> small breasts -> medium breasts -> big breasts -> hyper breasts in that order.

ball size follows about the same as breast size.

it offers flaccid, erect, foreskin (retracted, partially retracted, unretracted).

it's not great at micropenis so watch out for that.

animal genitals work as well if your into that (canine/equine).

you're gonna need to use an artist name as a base, i use ricegnat for a more "waifu" look. but just about any artist on E621 with more than 50 images should work fine, you can even blend them by adding multiple artists!

noise offset was used, so you get great contrast!

the VAE i used was vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned, but you can experiment with others!

in the event of too much furry bleed through make sure to add "anthro, fur, tail" in the negative prompt or human in the prompt.

enjoy everyone!

items.name: Sergal LoRA
items.description:
I've cobbled together a sergal LoRA in the hopes of seeing more art from other sergal enjoyers. These cheese dragons deserve some love!

Use weights for LoRA from 0.5 to 0.7 or it will overcook the image.

It was trained on the YiffyMix v2 model and performs best with it since it already has a good affinity for sergals. Other models I've tried were not as good.

It should be pretty versatile for both females and males. The main tag is 'sergal' but there is also a strong affinity for 'messy hair', 'fluffy', 'open mouth' and 'tongue out'.

You can add 'flat chested' for more classic sergal female gens.

The main problem, besides occasional extra digits on paws, is tails. They are long and curly, and SD very often makes double tails or even circle tails. You can try using remedies like 'multiple tails' and 'badly drawn tail' in the negatives but it's mostly a placebo.

You ask about, khm, ‘clitoral hood’? Ah, I see you're a person of culture as well. The data and tagging are there, but I did not manage to get anything that is not extremely cursed. So, sorry, maybe next time.
